Today, I am privileged to preside over the election of judges of the International Court of Justice at the Security Council, the procedure of which is complicated and unique compared with other elections of international organizations.
Congratulations to all those elected judges from Mexico, the United States, Australia, Romania, and South Africa respectively. I pay tribute to all candidates nominated for this election. In particular, I wish to thank the staff of the Secretariat for their professional and efficient function, without which the election would not be carried out so smoothly.

As part of its latest climate actions, China will launch carbon-peaking pilot projects in 100 cities and zones nationwide. The projects will explore innovative practices and reform measures for green and low-carbon development, which could then play a vital supportive role for carbon peaking at the national level.

In the first three quarters of 2023, China’s renewable energy installed capacity increased by 20% year-on-year to 1.384 bln KW, accounting for 49.6% of total installed capacity and exceeding that of thermal power.

legacy.full_text:
USG Voronkov was pleased to meet with H.E. Zhang Jun, @chinaambun to discuss 🇺🇳-🇨🇳 collaboration on #CounterTerrorism. 

He thanked #China 🇨🇳 for its strong support to @un_oct through the #UNPDF. 

Both stressed the importance of #multilateralism & joint efforts. https://t.co/F0BFgWFwr7

Glad to meet with USG Voronkov.

Multilateral cooperation is essential to effectively counter terrorism, which is a common enemy of humanity.

🇨🇳 supports UN in playing a central coordinating role in global CT efforts, and will continue to work with @UN_OCT to #CounterTerrorism.
